Are you saying THIS software has virus?

It isn't a virus, but a false positive reading.  The "virus" he's referring to is the Process.exe file.  When scanning files such as this one, which is a "command line process utility" used to shut down processes (in this case, the Virus Burst processes), some virus programs will label it as a PUP (Potentially Unwanted File).  

In other words, virus utilities cannot always tell if the " motives" of some files are malicious or good. This is why we dont automatically delete every single file the virus programs label as  *possibly* a bad file.  

After ridding the system of Virus Burst, you can safely delete the SmitFraudFix files from your computer.
